node.text: The fun projects, family time, making memories at home, and of course the last time I had a pedicure.😂Remembering the good things about 2020 before we welcome a fresh new start! #lifeonprairiehill

node.text:
Grab a cup of hot tea and come join me for a cozy little rainy day tour!💛I figured, hey, you’ve seen this place in the sun a thousand times. But once in awhile a quiet, cozy moment by candlelight is fun too!💛Are you in?
.
#fallhometour#rainyday#falldecor#yellowprairie#prairiehillfarm

node.text:
Let’s get crafty, punkin!💛Shopped our local Dollar Tree & came up with a fun little afternoon project. I love having somewhere to display a Bible verse, family pic, or favorite quote on my kitchen window sill...so I thought I’d make a few of these as gifts too! Whatcha think? LET THE CRAFTING SEASON BEGIN🙌🏻💛🙌🏻💛🙌🏻💛
.
#dollartreechallenge#crafty#fallcrafts#stencilproject#beforeandafter#prairiecrafts#yellowprairie#yellowprairiestyle#diy#diyhomedecor

node.text:
Creeper status??😂Before we owned the farm, we’d grab drive thru breakfast and park in the driveway here & stare at the house (it was unoccupied). We talked about all the things we’d do if we bought it...paint it white? Add a garage? Completely gut it down to the studs to check for bad plumbing or dead bodies?😂It was such fun to dream together. While trespassing. And wolfing down egg McMuffins. OH COME ON YOU’D DO IT TOO.😂😂
.

node.text:
Happy 131st birthday to our old girl!❤️We figured we’d bring her some red roses to celebrate.❤️Over the weekend we drove to multiple nurseries looking for these Double Knockout Red Roses after seeing them at the cutest historic cottage while on vacation. It feels like it was always meant to be.❤️❤️❤️Swipe for a few more views and to see the house on the day we bought it in 2017!❤️
.

A week away to...
💛eat all the carbs (like ALL of them)
💛hike in the rain
💛float in the sun
💛set down the phone 
💛BE WITH THE FAM
The best. Happy to be home & our hearts are full (and the pants are TIGHT *refer back to carb statement).😂
.
@baileymakaimokuphoto thanks for meeting us in this beautiful field to capture the moment.💛

node.text:
Our cutie pie @simpsondoorco Dutch door got a little sidekick today!😍 This patio off the garage needed some FUN so I found myself rifling through the attic to find a sign we no longer use...and gave it a new look! Did you follow along in stories?
.
3 things about the above caption make me wanna PINCH myself. 
-Dutch door
-Garage
-Attic
One of the only things we didn’t love about the farm when we found it almost 4 years ago was the LACK OF A GARAGE. Late last summer our garage construction got underway and we STILL can’t believe it’s here. Graced with our very favorite #simpsondoorco doors.😍
.

node.text: Turning 48 today and celebrating with a few “skip days”😂...do you spread your birthday out for a week too? (I won’t tell) Yesterday my daughter and I snuck over to the coast for the afternoon (swipe) and we have zero regrets about eating chips in the sunshine and dipping our toes in the chilly Pacific.🌊Today’s plan: some light vacuuming and a high calorie meal with the fam😂. #itsthesimplethings

node.text:
Our bathroom was a bustling construction zone today😂thanks to a pesky leak (see stories)...but good news. The 115 degree temps should help dry the walls out quickly and tomorrow we’ll be back to a friendlier 90 degree range. I love a summer adventure, don’t you??😂😂
.

node.text:
As kids, my sisters and I weren’t allowed to watch tv during the day (except Brady Bunch after school😂). We were expected to be outside helping on the farm, or riding bikes, or playing in the fresh air. (Mom & Dad truly did know best.💛) I think of those days often and how a root beer popsicle on the porch was allllmost better than watching Marcia & Greg fighting over who would get to have their bedroom in the attic.😂Raise your hand if you like tv-free summer days but can still appreciate the Brady Bunch.💁🏻‍♀️😂
.
